%^BOLD%^Suggested Readings:
%^BOLD%^%^GREEN%^Faiths and Avatars
%^BOLD%^%^GREEN%^Powers and Pantheons

%^BOLD%^%^BLUE%^The majority of the information about the gods of Shadowgate have been taken from these two books.  Not everything presented in these helpful tools from Wizards of the Coast are used, such as the Time of Troubles.  

%^BOLD%^We have taken some liberties with the faiths here:
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Akadi is the combination of Akadi and Valkur
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Bane is the combination of Bane and Hoar
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Beshaba is the combination of Beshaba, Moander, and Talona
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Cyric is the combination of Cyric, Garagos, and Velsharoon
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Grumbar is the combination of Gond, Geb, and Grumbar
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Istishia is the combination of Eldath, Umberlee, and Istishia
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Kossuth is the combination of Kossuth, Gargauth, and Glautru
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Mystra is Pre-Midnight
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Oghma is the combination of Milil, Denier, and Oghma
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Shar is the combination of Shar and Loviatar
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Tempus is the combination of Tempus and Uthgar
%^BOLD%^-%^GREEN%^Torm is the combination of Torm, Ilmater, and Nobanion
